WEBVTT

00:30.306 --> 00:32.049
Hello, welcome to God Day.

00:32.850 --> 00:49.357
I'm Derek Walker, the pastor of the Oxford Bible Church, and I want to share about prophecy, end-time prophecy, messianic prophecy, and understanding the time that we live in.

00:50.318 --> 00:57.490
And one aspect that I find very helpful is to understand

00:59.138 --> 01:03.524
what the church age is about, the origin of the church age that we live in.

01:03.564 --> 01:04.665
Will it go on forever?

01:05.546 --> 01:07.549
Or will it come to an end?

01:08.210 --> 01:10.553
And what's going to happen next?

01:11.474 --> 01:17.202
And to understand this, we need to get the big picture of Bible prophecy.

01:17.983 --> 01:23.410
And the Old Testament prophets, let's start with them because we

01:23.650 --> 01:27.695
A big part of the Christian world does not take the Old Testament prophet seriously.

01:27.755 --> 01:31.759
They kind of spiritualize their prophecies.

01:32.340 --> 01:40.269
But what the Old Testament prophets saw, we could describe, it's just like someone who is looking at two mountains in the distance.

01:41.210 --> 01:52.402
And, you know, if you ever have been in the Alps or somewhere like that, looking at mountains in the distance, you're looking at two mountains.

01:52.610 --> 01:54.092
But it looks like one mountain.

01:54.612 --> 01:56.094
It's like they're next to each other.

01:56.475 --> 02:05.726
And it's only when you climb over the first mountain that you find that there's a big valley in between before the next mountain.

02:05.746 --> 02:09.571
And you realize you've got a lot more climbing to do than what you imagined.

02:10.071 --> 02:13.135
And the Old Testament prophets were looking forwards in time.

02:13.175 --> 02:20.304
And what they essentially saw was two mountains, which we call the sufferings and the glory of the Messiah.

02:20.785 --> 02:21.906
They saw

02:23.394 --> 02:38.732
the Messiah, Jesus, come the first time in His first coming as the suffering Savior, as the sacrifice for our sins, as the Lamb of God who would die for our sins.

02:39.493 --> 02:42.757
And they saw what we call the suffering Messiah.

02:42.877 --> 02:50.226
And so there's a whole lot of prophecies that describe Jesus coming in His first coming, which of course Jesus has already fulfilled.

02:50.594 --> 02:52.317
that he'd be born in Bethlehem.

02:52.377 --> 02:53.639
He'd live a perfect life.

02:53.719 --> 02:58.866
He would die as our sacrifice, like in Isaiah 53.

03:00.088 --> 03:08.461
But also, they looked further into the future, and they also saw the Messiah in his glory.

03:09.583 --> 03:11.606
And it's called the sufferings and the glory.

03:12.026 --> 03:19.858
And the mountain peak further away, it was a vision of him coming to the earth.

03:20.034 --> 03:48.786
in power and glory as the conquering king, as the king of kings and he's coming to reign on earth and he would establish his kingdom on earth called the messianic kingdom and both of these are true prophecies of the future but what they prophets couldn't see was the time in between just like you can't see that valley in between and so they didn't know if

03:48.898 --> 03:59.070
the conquering Messiah would happen, you know, straight after the suffering Messiah, or if there would be a long time in between.

03:59.771 --> 04:03.736
And there was a reason that God kept this time in between.

04:04.157 --> 04:05.558
God calls it a mystery.

04:06.159 --> 04:18.354
We know it now as the church age, the mystery of the church, or the mystery of the church age, which is described especially by the Apostle Paul as a mystery that

04:18.466 --> 04:21.530
is hidden in God from the foundation of the world.

04:21.550 --> 04:24.614
There's a reason why God kept that a secret.

04:25.355 --> 04:38.393
And it's due to, well, the basic reason for that is that God had to keep it a secret because it all depended on whether Israel would accept her Messiah or not.

04:39.114 --> 04:45.463
We're, you know, basically to cut a long story short.

04:45.623 --> 04:47.666
When Jesus came the first time,

04:47.810 --> 04:50.493
when he preached the kingdom of God is at hand.

04:51.114 --> 04:54.978
He wasn't just talking to individuals, the gospel of the kingdom.

04:55.378 --> 05:03.787
He was actually addressing the nation and he's saying, I am the Messiah and I am ready to establish my kingdom.

05:04.788 --> 05:13.618
And of course he had to die and rise again first, but had the leadership of Israel accepted him as the Messiah, he

05:13.730 --> 05:22.541
would be obliged by the covenants, especially the Davidic covenant to establish his kingdom then, the Messianic kingdom.

05:23.362 --> 05:38.661
And he would reign on earth from Jerusalem and bring in the wonderful kingdom of peace that is promised by the prophets, the time of restoration of all things.

05:39.502 --> 05:43.026
And in fact, Orthodox Jews will criticize

05:43.362 --> 05:52.995
the, you know, Christianity, they'll say, Jesus can't be the Messiah because when Jesus came, he didn't establish a kingdom of peace.

05:53.015 --> 05:54.617
We've had 2000 years of wars.

05:55.558 --> 05:57.040
And in a sense, they have a point.

05:57.181 --> 06:10.258
But what they, what they didn't, what they don't realize is that he first had to come as the suffering Messiah and that for that kingdom to be established, Israel have to receive them as the Messiah.

06:10.914 --> 06:22.285
And because they rejected him as a nation, they rejected him instead of bringing in the kingdom, God postponed the kingdom and instead he brought in the church age.

06:22.406 --> 06:24.888
Now, for God, it wasn't a surprise.

06:25.529 --> 06:35.759
God knew from the foundation of the world that this would happen, but he couldn't reveal it in advance because that would remove Israel's free will.

06:35.819 --> 06:38.802
If God already, you know,

06:38.882 --> 06:46.431
If God said to you, you know, I want you to do this, but I'm telling you in advance, you're going to reject my will and you're not going to do it.

06:46.451 --> 06:48.573
Then there's no room for your free will.

06:49.094 --> 07:00.848
So God gave Israel the offer of the kingdom, but he didn't reveal and he doesn't reveal if they're going to accept or reject.

07:00.948 --> 07:05.874
So it's when Israel rejected Jesus that he started revealing

07:07.330 --> 07:10.714
that the church age would come in instead of the kingdom.

07:11.254 --> 07:16.881
And so this valley in between those two mountains is already about 2,000 years.

07:16.921 --> 07:19.404
And I believe we're very near the end of that valley now.

07:20.385 --> 07:23.869
And God has not changed his purposes.

07:25.130 --> 07:31.497
The church age is not the ultimate thing as far as the history of the earth is concerned, the history of mankind.

07:31.557 --> 07:35.762
God will fulfill his purpose for the church age.

07:35.842 --> 07:42.952
of saving many from all the nations and then he will bring in his kingdom program.

07:43.473 --> 07:52.987
He will, there'll be the tribulation, the day of the Lord, God will move in judgment and save, have a final harvest in the tribulation.

07:53.828 --> 08:00.498
And then Jesus will come in power and glory as the Kingly Messiah and establish his kingdom on earth.

08:01.058 --> 08:10.210
But right now we're living in that valley between those two mountains and I think it just helps to understand that in terms of having a big picture.

08:10.671 --> 08:13.815
We live between the two comings of the Messiah.

08:14.136 --> 08:17.360
He's coming as the Lamb and then he's coming as the Lion.

08:17.961 --> 08:21.546
And that's exactly what 1P the 1.10 says.

08:22.807 --> 08:24.850
Basically the prophets saw

08:25.026 --> 08:29.630
the suffering Messiah, the glorious Messiah, but they didn't see the valley in between.

08:30.011 --> 08:32.333
That was a mystery hidden in God.

08:33.094 --> 08:43.103
And one Peter 1 10 says of this salvation, and this is the new covenant salvation that the Messiah will bring in through His first covenant, the new covenant in His blood.

08:43.844 --> 08:46.166
This is prophesied in Jeremiah 31.

08:46.466 --> 08:48.148
It's prophesied in Ezekiel 36.

08:48.288 --> 08:54.834
It's prophesied in many passages, the coming of the new covenant through the Messiah.

08:55.458 --> 09:03.674
Peter again says, of this salvation, the prophets having quiet and searched carefully who prophesied of the grace that would come to you.

09:04.155 --> 09:07.762
So the prophets predicted the blessings of the new covenant.

09:08.905 --> 09:17.682
And then verse 11 it says, what the prophets did was that they were searching what time and what kind of time

09:18.722 --> 09:28.796
the Spirit of Christ who was in them was indicating when he testified beforehand of the sufferings of Christ and the glories that would follow.

09:29.377 --> 09:46.962
And this is saying that the prophets saw the sufferings of Christ in his first coming and his glories as the conquering king in the second coming, but they could not see the time period in between, the valley in between these two comings, that we now know as the church age.

09:47.586 --> 09:51.291
It wasn't clear to them, first of all, what time?

09:51.892 --> 09:54.576
In other words, how long this time period would be?

09:55.597 --> 10:01.326
And also, would it be days, years, millennia, centuries?

10:01.366 --> 10:04.310
And also it says, what kind of time?

10:05.011 --> 10:07.134
What is the nature of that time?

10:07.194 --> 10:08.536
What would happen in that time?

10:09.698 --> 10:14.504
Because it's not the Messianic Kingdom, it's something else, but it was hidden to them.

10:14.745 --> 10:15.666
It was a mystery.

10:16.034 --> 10:21.983
God had to keep it a mystery until Israel made their decision to accept or reject the Messiah.

10:22.884 --> 10:30.876
And that's why when you read prophecies, they often jump from the first coming to the second coming.

10:31.237 --> 10:36.585
And they jump over the valley in between because the prophets can't see the gap in between.

10:36.605 --> 10:40.731
So you're reading about the first coming, then suddenly it jumps to the second coming.

10:41.332 --> 10:42.674
You know, an example of that.

10:43.042 --> 10:46.966
is a famous prophecy, you know, Isaiah 9, 6, and 7.

10:47.707 --> 11:01.060
So Isaiah 9, 6, for example, is primarily, really, about the first coming of Christ, for unto us a child is born, unto us a son is given, and his name will be called wonderful, that, in other words, miracle worker.

11:01.941 --> 11:04.283
Counselor, which means he'll be a teacher.

11:05.164 --> 11:06.065
Mighty God.

11:06.345 --> 11:08.147
Yes, he's an Elgabor, the mighty God.

11:08.888 --> 11:11.090
Everlasting father, or literally

11:11.170 --> 11:15.855
source of everlasting life and prince of peace.

11:16.676 --> 11:23.322
So this really describes his first coming and then suddenly the prophecy jumps 2,000 years.

11:23.423 --> 11:26.386
It jumps over that mystery time, that valley.

11:27.567 --> 11:34.053
At verse 7 it says, of the increase of his government and peace there will be no end.

11:35.335 --> 11:38.578
And this is not describing the church age actually.

11:38.818 --> 11:46.710
This is describing the future Messianic Kingdom, which is in Revelation 20, we're told it will last for 1,000 years.

11:46.770 --> 11:48.713
He'll reign on earth for 1,000 years.

11:49.595 --> 11:53.941
And this is the increase of his government peace and there'll be no end.

11:54.382 --> 12:01.253
And the proof that it's a future kingdom is upon the throne of David and over his kingdom.

12:01.273 --> 12:02.034
In other words,

12:02.210 --> 12:15.610
This will be the fulfillment of God's promise to David in the Davidic covenant that one of his sons will sit on the throne of David and over the kingdom of David.

12:16.051 --> 12:19.336
And that is an earthly throne and an earthly kingdom.

12:19.356 --> 12:24.604
You see, Jesus is sitting on a throne right now, but it's the throne of his father in heaven.

12:25.185 --> 12:28.850
But the throne of David is the throne of the earth.

12:29.154 --> 12:36.684
The throne of that David rules over Israel and the Messiah will rule over not just Israel, but the whole earth, the whole world.

12:37.425 --> 12:42.552
But this will only be fulfilled at the second coming of Christ.

12:42.953 --> 12:45.256
So verse six is the first coming.

12:45.656 --> 12:47.679
Verse seven, it jumps to the second coming.

12:48.801 --> 12:55.730
Upon the throne of David and over his kingdom to order it and establish it with judgment and justice from that time forward, even forever.

12:55.938 --> 13:05.267
praise God and the kingdom of God will last that thousand years and then the kingdom of God will continue under Christ into all eternity.

13:05.987 --> 13:11.473
And so from the Old Testament prophets, there is a clear sequence of four things.

13:11.573 --> 13:16.197
First of all, Christ's first coming to suffer and die for our salvation.

13:16.878 --> 13:21.842
Then there will be a mystery age, a mystery time that we know as the church age now.

13:22.603 --> 13:25.906
Then will be his second coming in power and glory

13:26.402 --> 13:35.536
when he establishes his kingdom on earth, and then fourthly, the Messianic kingdom itself, that we now know as the millennium.

13:36.297 --> 13:45.211
And so, this issue is one of the major issues of prophecy.

13:47.094 --> 13:48.356
You see, the puzzle is this.

13:49.498 --> 13:54.866
The prophets predicted the Messianic kingdom, but when the Messiah actually came,

13:55.938 --> 13:58.081
He didn't establish the Messianic Kingdom.

13:58.862 --> 13:59.202
Why?

14:00.023 --> 14:02.947
And instead, he established the church age.

14:03.788 --> 14:12.560
And the reason is because the kingdom, the Messianic Kingdom is established in fulfillment of the covenants to Israel.

14:12.881 --> 14:19.309
And because Israel rejected her Messiah, it wasn't possible for God to establish the Messianic Kingdom at that time.

14:19.950 --> 14:21.652
But God was not taken by surprise.

14:21.712 --> 14:23.194
He knew what would happen all the time.

14:23.615 --> 14:25.938
And from eternity, he actually planned

14:26.050 --> 14:35.382
for what we now call the church age, in which God's purpose is to save as many as possible from all the nations.

14:36.183 --> 14:40.748
Anyway, these Messianic issues came to a head in Matthew chapter 16.

14:40.788 --> 14:49.379
And this was a very important time when God went to Caesarea, Christ led his disciples to Caesarea Philippi.

14:49.980 --> 14:55.186
And we see in this passage that the disciples did not understand

14:55.810 --> 14:57.952
that what was going to happen.

14:58.253 --> 15:08.625
You know, they were just expecting Jesus the Messiah to be the conquering Messiah and they were expecting Him as it were to just take over the world and they'll rule with Him.

15:09.245 --> 15:12.870
They didn't really understand that He would have to suffer and die first.

15:13.651 --> 15:20.178
And so He had been hinting at that but now He makes it very clear because by this time in Matthew

15:20.322 --> 15:29.733
In fact, it was already very clear in Matthew chapter 12 when the Jewish leaders accused Jesus of being possessed by Satan.

15:30.513 --> 15:32.195
And he warned them then.

15:32.235 --> 15:38.242
He said, you're in great danger of committing the unforgivable sin of rejecting me.

15:39.023 --> 15:39.904
And he warned them.

15:40.705 --> 15:48.914
They hadn't quite crossed the line yet, but he said, I'm going to give you one more sign, which is the sign of Jonah, which was his death and resurrection.

15:49.890 --> 15:56.438
the time would come after his resurrection when Israel would officially reject him as the Messiah.

15:58.661 --> 16:02.606
And so what was God going to do in that situation?

16:03.287 --> 16:07.893
Well, in Matthew 16, it's clear that he was being rejected.

16:07.913 --> 16:18.226
And so for the first time in verse 18, Christ revealed that he was going to bring something new that had not been revealed before.

16:19.106 --> 16:25.434
He said, on this rock, and he's talking about himself, he is the foundation rock of the church.

16:25.894 --> 16:28.117
On this rock, I will build my church.

16:28.197 --> 16:29.559
So the church is a new thing.

16:30.180 --> 16:32.042
It's not Israel, it's a new thing.

16:32.122 --> 16:33.344
I will build my church.

16:34.165 --> 16:41.854
And on the foundation rock of himself through his death and resurrection, he will build his church.

16:42.835 --> 16:45.138
And then in verse 20,

16:45.698 --> 16:51.345
It says, he commanded his disciples that they should tell no one that he was Jesus the Christ.

16:52.166 --> 16:55.451
Now that might have puzzled you, why would he tell them not to say that?

16:56.131 --> 17:02.420
Well, the reason is that the title Christ, which means Messiah, had baggage for the Jews.

17:02.500 --> 17:07.807
The Jews were looking for the Messiah, but they were looking for the conquering Messiah.

17:08.307 --> 17:10.009
But he had come to suffer and die.

17:10.590 --> 17:13.554
So if they would have been proclaiming Jesus is the Christ,

17:13.762 --> 17:18.467
then all the crowds would have followed Jesus because they expected him to take on the Romans.

17:19.288 --> 17:22.291
And of course, that was not the intention.

17:22.311 --> 17:24.053
That would have been a massive distraction.

17:24.854 --> 17:31.582
And so he said, don't tell them right now that I'm the Christ because of that, that would be misunderstood.

17:32.162 --> 17:42.834
But of course, after his death and resurrection, they preached that Jesus is the Christ because then it would be understood what it means.

17:43.682 --> 17:50.302
What Christ means, it means that He would first suffer, die, rise again, and that He will come again in power and glory.

17:50.703 --> 17:51.265
Praise God.

17:51.285 --> 17:57.042
So it's interesting that He needed even His disciples to know this truth.

17:57.218 --> 17:59.780
that he first had to come as the suffering Messiah.

17:59.800 --> 18:16.276
And so in verse 21 of Matthew 16, he said, from that time, Jesus began to show to his disciples that he must go to Jerusalem and suffer many things from the elders, chief priests and scribes, and be killed and be raised the third day.

18:16.917 --> 18:26.866
So notice he is now telling them that first he must fulfill the prophecies of the suffering Messiah, which they were not expecting.

18:27.234 --> 18:29.698
And that's why Peter rebuked him in verse 22.

18:29.778 --> 18:36.648
It says, then Peter took him aside, began to rebuke him, saying, far be it from you, Lord, this should not happen to you.

18:36.688 --> 18:39.372
In other words, they did not understand.

18:40.274 --> 18:46.904
Like the rest of the Jews, they ignored the prophecies of the suffering Messiah, they were just interested in the Kingly Messiah.

18:47.685 --> 18:51.491
And so Jesus had to correct them on that.

18:52.272 --> 18:56.338
And so he's saying, I'm going to have to suffer and die, but I will rise again.

18:57.058 --> 19:03.726
And then he confirmed that he would still fulfill the prophecies of the Kingly Messiah, but that would take place later.

19:04.527 --> 19:13.659
He said in verse 27, for the Son of Man will come in the glory of his father with his angels, and then he will reward everyone according to his works.

19:14.480 --> 19:26.194
So notice, he is still affirming, the time will come when I will return in my glory as the glorious Messiah, but he didn't reveal

19:26.338 --> 19:28.421
what the time period would be.

19:28.441 --> 19:44.160
And then he said a bit of a prophetic paradox here in verse 28, he said, shortly I say to you, there are some standing here who shall not taste death till they see the Son of Man coming in his kingdom.

19:45.181 --> 19:53.231
So he is confirming to them, although he's going to suffer and die, he will still fulfill the kingdom prophecies.

19:54.372 --> 19:55.954
He will establish his kingdom.

19:56.450 --> 20:04.882
And then he says, as a proof of that, there are some standing here who will not die till they see me in my kingdom glory.

20:05.763 --> 20:11.010
And people said, oh, that's a false prophecy because Jesus hasn't returned.

20:11.471 --> 20:15.356
He didn't say that every eye will see him in his lifetime.

20:15.717 --> 20:17.880
He said that some will see him.

20:18.380 --> 20:25.330
And the solution to this puzzle, how was this fulfilled, is if you just keep reading on,

20:25.794 --> 20:30.258
You'll see in Matthew chapter 17 how that was fulfilled.

20:30.319 --> 20:39.888
In fact, it was fulfilled by the transfiguration because unfortunately there's a chapter break between that verse and then the next verses.

20:40.329 --> 20:43.011
But if we just carry reading on, we'll see exactly.

20:43.612 --> 20:49.398
Matthew 17 verse one says, now after six days, Jesus took Peter, James and John.

20:49.458 --> 20:53.842
Those are the some, you see, that we'll see him in his kingdom glory.

20:54.306 --> 21:00.373
He took Peter, James and John up a high mountain by themselves and he was transfigured before them.

21:00.814 --> 21:08.403
His face shone like the sun and his clothes became as white as light and behold Moses and Elijah appeared to them talking with them.

21:09.224 --> 21:23.762
And so what was going on here is that because he knew that they would see him in weakness, in humility, suffering and dying, that they could be discouraged.

21:23.842 --> 21:25.023
it all failed.

21:25.884 --> 21:31.151
But actually, he gave them a prophetic preview in the Transfiguration.

21:31.531 --> 21:38.559
He gave a prophetic preview of him in his kingly glory and his future kingdom.

21:38.659 --> 21:51.314
He was assuring them that although he would suffer and die, he would also rise again and he will also come again as the King of Kings and the Lord of Lords.

21:51.522 --> 21:56.428
this vision of the transfiguration was a visible confirmation of that.

21:57.089 --> 21:58.932
And that's how Peter interpreted it.

21:59.372 --> 22:15.754
When you go to 2 Peter chapter 1 verse 16 to 19, it says, we did not follow cunningly devised fables when we made known to you the power and the coming, the future coming, the second coming of our Lord Jesus Christ.

22:16.334 --> 22:19.058
He says, but we were eyewitnesses.

22:19.362 --> 22:20.624
of his majesty.

22:20.664 --> 22:22.426
That means his kingly glory.

22:22.946 --> 22:25.670
We were eyewitnesses of his kingly glory.

22:25.690 --> 22:30.255
They had the preview of that kingdom.

22:30.996 --> 22:42.130
For he received from God honor and glory when such a voice came to him from the excellent glory, saying, this is my beloved son in whom I am well pleased.

22:42.498 --> 22:47.245
And we heard this voice which came from heaven when we were with him on the holy mountain.

22:47.686 --> 22:50.430
And so we have the prophetic word confirmed.

22:50.751 --> 22:59.985
In other words, the prophets declared that there was this coming messianic kingdom, the Messiah will reign on earth in his glory.

23:00.566 --> 23:04.752
And he's saying that was confirmed by the transfiguration.

23:05.073 --> 23:06.355
God confirmed it to us.

23:06.755 --> 23:07.276
Praise God.

23:08.758 --> 23:11.122
And so the transfiguration was his

23:11.490 --> 23:19.883
assurance to them that although he would die as the suffering servant, he will indeed return to reign in power and glory.

23:19.903 --> 23:21.725
And that should really encourage us.

23:21.765 --> 23:30.879
But whatever mess the world is in right now, we're not here to take over the world, but we are here to save as many as possible.

23:31.380 --> 23:38.130
But the day is coming when Jesus will return and judge this world and establish his kingdom.

23:38.530 --> 23:43.877
of peace on the earth and he'll reign for a thousand years and we will reign with him, Hallelujah.

23:44.958 --> 23:54.070
And so this is a picture and notice some aspects of this picture.

23:55.231 --> 24:03.442
First of all, you will see Christ, the glorified Christ, as he will be in his kingdom on earth.

24:03.554 --> 24:11.244
And we see that he is under his father's authority, because the father speaks from above saying, this is my beloved son, listen to him.

24:11.725 --> 24:31.250
In other words, the father is the highest authority, but he's backing up Jesus in his authority and commanding everyone in this kingdom to obey, listen to and obey Jesus, because he is the king, the ordained king by God.

24:31.362 --> 24:33.425
then you see people like Moses.

24:34.146 --> 24:37.490
You see people in their natural bodies will be in that kingdom.

24:38.111 --> 24:44.280
There will be natural people who survive the tribulation in that kingdom represented by Peter, James and John.

24:45.141 --> 24:49.547
And then you will also see glorified saints like Moses and Elijah.

24:50.288 --> 24:57.177
You see, they represent the glorified saints which will be like us in that kingdom.

24:57.257 --> 25:00.722
Moses died and then so

25:01.442 --> 25:08.154
Moses there is a picture of the resurrected saints, whereas Elijah was raptured as it were.

25:08.675 --> 25:10.538
And so he's a picture of the raptured saints.

25:10.558 --> 25:26.226
So the glorified saints who will rule and reign with Christ will be those who are the resurrected and also those who are raptured while they're still alive, praise God, and we will be in glory with Christ.

25:26.498 --> 25:30.683
ruling and reign with him over the people in their natural bodies.

25:30.743 --> 25:33.986
